{"_id":"Sz1MVwyGSsTCSh5w","name":"Fragment of the Yellow Compass","type":"gift","img":"icons/sundries/misc/compass-brass-blue-brown.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.fragment-of-the-yellow-compass","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":1,"folderName":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You possess the western (yellow) piece of the Compass Rose that Margareta guarded. This golden needle hums with temporal energy and points toward the nearest Compass Rose piece (currently southeast toward Helga's red piece in Rot). While carrying this fragment, you experience temporal echoes: glimpses of past and future in this location. Once per Scene, consult the fragment to receive a vision—GM reveals one useful fact about the immediate past or near future. Warning: carrying Compass Rose pieces makes you a target for those seeking to control time itself.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Obtained from Margareta (through persuasion, combat, or inheriting after her death)</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Visions are fragmentary and open to interpretation. Fragment grows heavier as you collect more pieces (physical burden of temporal power). Henkle can sense when pieces are brought together.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> temporal, navigation, visions, artifact</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.fragment-of-the-yellow-compass","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["temporal","navigation","visions","artifact"],"requirements":"Obtained from Margareta (through persuasion, combat, or inheriting after her death)","limitations":"Visions are fragmentary and open to interpretation. Fragment grows heavier as you collect more pieces (physical burden of temporal power). Henkle can sense when pieces are brought together."},"sort":400000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332110,"modifiedTime":1784280332110,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"TQK7AiJnBbs6DFnF","name":"Sanctuary of Gelb","type":"gift","img":"icons/environment/settlement/house-small.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.sanctuary-of-gelb","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":2,"folderName":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>You have earned the trust and gratitude of the outcasts in the village of Gelb. The villagers—people with leontiasis, elephantiasis, severe burns, missing limbs—see you as protector rather than threat. While in Gelb, you have sanctuary: free lodging, meals, basic medical care. Villagers warn you of dangers, share rumors about Rot and Smaragd, offer their unique skills. Once per scenario, call upon a villager's specialized knowledge (herbalism, tracking, local history). If Margareta survived, she provides magical insight. If she died protecting them, they honor you as her successor and will risk their lives to help you stop Henkle.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Save Klaus from kidnappers, show compassion to outcasts, or defeat those threatening Gelb</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>Villagers are not warriors—they provide support, not combat aid. If you betray their trust or harm them, lose this gift permanently. Henkle or OZena may target Gelb to hurt you.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> social, sanctuary, allies, knowledge</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.sanctuary-of-gelb","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["social","sanctuary","allies","knowledge"],"requirements":"Save Klaus from kidnappers, show compassion to outcasts, or defeat those threatening Gelb","limitations":"Villagers are not warriors—they provide support, not combat aid. If you betray their trust or harm them, lose this gift permanently. Henkle or OZena may target Gelb to hurt you."},"sort":500000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332112,"modifiedTime":1784280332112,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
{"_id":"4ArAPLTOTUJnRVBT","name":"Traveler from Tomorrow","type":"gift","img":"icons/magic/time/clock-stopwatch-white-gray.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"flags":{"broken-tales":{"category":"scenario-gift","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","contentKey":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.traveler-from-tomorrow","role":"scenario-gift","sequence":3,"folderName":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village"}},"system":{"description":"<h3>Scenario Gift</h3><p>Through encounters with OZena, Lowe, Hirnloser, and Dose, you've learned they're from the future (early 1900s America). You can recognize anachronistic references: when Hirnloser mentions 'electricity' or Dose talks about 'hospitals,' you understand these are things that don't exist yet in 1780. Once per Scene, leverage your knowledge of their future origin: gain +1 to Social Checks when convincing them you know their secret, recognize which of OZena's behaviors are desperate cries for help versus true malice, identify objects or knowledge that came from their era. This gift represents empathy—understanding they're displaced and suffering, not inherently evil.</p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>Have meaningful conversation with at least one time-displaced character, piece together clues about their origin</p><h3>Limitations</h3><p>This knowledge doesn't grant future technology or science. You understand they're from the future but can't replicate their world. Henkle will become hostile if he realizes you know too much.</p><p><strong>Tags:</strong> knowledge, social, empathy, time-travel</p>","notes":"Scenario Gift - Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","somaCost":0,"automaticSuccesses":0,"owner":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","source":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","category":"scenario-gift","key":"scenario-gift.ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village.traveler-from-tomorrow","scenario":"Ozena, the Suffering and Desperate - Part One: The Yellow Village","scenarioSlug":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate-part-one-the-yellow-village","sourceDirectory":"ozena-the-suffering-and-desperate","tags":["knowledge","social","empathy","time-travel"],"requirements":"Have meaningful conversation with at least one time-displaced character, piece together clues about their origin","limitations":"This knowledge doesn't grant future technology or science. You understand they're from the future but can't replicate their world. Henkle will become hostile if he realizes you know too much."},"sort":600000,"ownership":{"default":0},"_stats":{"compendiumSource":null,"duplicateSource":null,"coreVersion":"14.365","systemId":"broken-tales","systemVersion":"0.2.17","createdTime":1784280332113,"modifiedTime":1784280332113,"lastModifiedBy":null,"exportSource":null}}
